.TH "scsi_report_opcode" 9 "scsi_report_opcode" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
scsi_report_opcode \- Find out if a given command opcode is supported
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" scsi_report_opcode
.BI "(struct scsi_device *sdev "  ","
.BI "unsigned char *buffer "  ","
.BI "unsigned int len "  ","
.BI "unsigned char opcode "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sdev" 12
scsi device to query
.IP "buffer" 12
scratch buffer (must be at least 20 bytes long)
.IP "len" 12
length of buffer
.IP "opcode" 12
opcode for command to look up
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Uses the REPORT SUPPORTED OPERATION CODES to look up the given
opcode. Returns -EINVAL if RSOC fails, 0 if the command opcode is
unsupported and 1 if the device claims to support the command.
